- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with wireless sensor networks and communication algorithms. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also likely as the paper discusses surveillance applications, which may involve security concerns. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is relevant as the paper deals with distributed targets and the shortest possible time to eliminate them. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper discusses decision-aware suppression methods. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is less likely but still possible as the paper may involve intelligent decision-making algorithms for the WSAN system.
